          "summary": "Authentic Chicken Enchiladas might be just the main course you are searching for. Watching your figure? This gluten free recipe has <b>332 calories</b>, <b>16g of protein</b>, and <b>10g of fat</b> per serving. For <b>$1.04 per serving</b>, this recipe <b>covers 13%</b> of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. A few people made this recipe, and 54 would say it hit the spot. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around <b>45 minutes</b>. This recipe is typical of Mexican cuisine. A mixture of onion, chili powder, corn tortillas, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so delicious. To use up the salt and pepper you could follow this main course with the <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/dr-pepper-cake-with-flour-cooked-frosting-539165\">Dr. Pepper Cake with Flour Cooked Frosting</a> as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe <b>deserves a spoonacular score of 69%</b>. This score is pretty good. Try <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/authentic-enchiladas-verdes-471722\">Authentic Enchiladas Verdes</a>, <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/authentic-enchiladas-verde-108087\">Authentic Enchiladas Verde</a>, and <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/authentic-mexican-enchiladas-verdes-108059\">Authentic Mexican Enchiladas Verdes</a> for similar recipes.",
