          "summary": "If you have approximately <b>approximately 45 minutes</b> to spend in the kitchen, Filipino Egg Rolls might be an awesome <b>gluten free and dairy free</b> recipe to try. For <b>$11.84 per serving</b>, you get a hor d'oeuvre that serves 1. One serving contains <b>2068 calories</b>, <b>113g of protein</b>, and <b>169g of fat</b>. This recipe from Foodista requires ground beef, shrimps, lumpia wrappers, and salt. 14 people were glad they tried this recipe. This recipe is typical of Chinese cuisine. Taking all factors into account, this recipe <b>earns a spoonacular score of 88%</b>, which is amazing. Similar recipes are <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/filipino-egg-rolls-94117\">Filipino Egg Rolls</a>, <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/filipino-egg-pie-566676\">Filipino Egg Pie</a>, and <a href=\"https://spoonacular.com/recipes/vegetarian-lumpia-filipino-spring-rolls-613414\">Vegetarian Lumpia (Filipino Spring Rolls)</a>.",
